Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm
wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the
@Lemon & Herb Seasoning{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss
to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, remove the @Slow Cooked British Pork{425%grams} from the packaging.
Place in an #ovenproof dish{} along with the juices and cover loosely with
#foil{}.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the pork is piping hot throughout.

While everything roasts, halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1/2%unit}(halved,
peeled and sliced) as thinly as you can.

Pop it into a small #bowl{} with the @red wine vinegar{12%grams} and @sugar{1%tsp}.
Add a pinch of salt, toss to combine, then set aside.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1%unit}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice. Pop
into a medium bowl and set aside for later.

Once cooked, remove the pork from the oven, reserving 1 tbsp of cooking juices
per person. Discard the foil and any remaining cooking juices.

Use two #forks{} to shred the pork as finely as you can, then stir through the
@chipotle paste{40%grams}(use less if you'd prefer things milder) and
@BBQ sauce{48%grams}. Season with salt and pepper.

When the chips are almost ready, pop the @plain taco tortillas{3.96} onto
a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @baby leaf mix{20%grams}, @soured cream{75%grams} and a
drizzle of oil to the bowl of baby gem. Season with salt and pepper, then toss
to coat.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

When everything's ready, share the tortillas between your plates and spread on
the @ma mayonnaise{2%tbsp}.

Share half the salad between your tortillas, then top with the chipotle pork
and a few slices of pickled onion.

Add the remaining pickled onion and the pickling liquid to the remaining salad.
Toss to combine.

Serve your tacos with the chips and salad alongside. Enjoy!